No-erased-levels-in-primitives-3.agda:29.3-69: error: [UnequalTypes]
The function types
  {@0 a : Level} {A : Set a} {x y : A} → x ≡ y → x ≡ y
and
  {a : Level} {A : Set a} {x z : A} → x ≡ z → x ≡ z
are not equal, because:
  one has erased domain, while the other is unrestricted.
when checking that the type of the primitive function
primEraseEquality is ∀ {@0 a} {A : Set a} {x y : A} → x ≡ y → x ≡ y
